Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

; This registry file sets the "Change what closing the lid does" option to "Do nothing" for both battery and AC power in Windows 10.

; Navigate to the Power key or create it if it doesn't exist.
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\PowerCfg\PowerPolicies\5]
; Set the "ACSettingIndex" DWORD value to 0 for the "lidaction" setting, which means "Do nothing" on AC power.
"lidaction_ACSettingIndex"=dword:00000000
; Set the "DCSettingIndex" DWORD value to 0 for the "lidaction" setting, which means "Do nothing" on battery power.
"lidaction_DCSettingIndex"=dword:00000000